cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper presents a framework for training sketch simplification networks using a discriminator network, which is a common approach in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised data and the optimization for a single image, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper presents user tests to validate the approach, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM).
